<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Phrase 1 (mm. 1-5): Light 2-note RH, 4-note LH in root position. Dm = D2-A2-D3-F3 open
  voicing (P5+P4+m3), G = G2-D3-G3-B3. Builds familiarity with the modal Dm centre.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 6-10): Fuller RH 3-note chords, LH same structure but with 7th color
  on Dm7 (bar 10). Suspension figure C→Em→F→C in bars 9/4.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 11-15): Development with quartal (G4-C5) on G chord, Am add9 suspension
  (bar 13), and climactic bar 14 with all 4 chords at full 4-voice texture.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 16-20): Csus4 opening (bar 16) for color; chromatic non-diatonic Bb
  substituted by IV(F) throughout bars 19-20.
- Phrase 5 (mm. 21-23): Full 8-voice texture, G with 5-note span, final Am whole note.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 4/9/17: inner voice descends C5-B4-A4-G4 in RH (2nds, smooth contrary motion vs LH)
- Bar 13: Am add9 (A4-B4-E5) creates stepwise suspension before Dm release
- Bar 14: all four chords in one bar — RH stays in 4th-string band (B4-C5) for minimal motion
- Bar 15: 8th-note sub-beat changes (Dm→Em in beat 1) — fastest voice-leading passage

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-5: Sparse opening (2+4 notes), introduces Dm-centric material
- mm. 6-10: Phrase repeat with richer RH (3 notes), 7th color on Dm7
- mm. 11-15: Development — quartal voicings (G), add9 suspension (Am), full 4-chord bar 14
- mm. 16-20: Color phrase — Csus4, wide-spaced Am, IV substitutions for Bb
- mm. 21-23: Grand return — widest spans, most notes per beat, final Am resolution
-->
